{{Other uses|Dgebuadze (disambiguation){{!}}Dgebuadze}}
'''Dgebuadze''' ({{lang-ka|დგებუაძე}}) was a [[Georgia (country)|Georgian]] noble family from the province of [[Mingrelia]]. In the 19th century, they served to the [[Dadiani]] [[Principality of Mingrelia|princes of Mingrelia]] as governors (''[[mouravi]]'') of the canton of [[Salipartiano]].<ref name=gse8>{{cite book|last1=Beradze|first1=Tamaz|title=ქართული საბჭოთა ენციკლოპედია, ტ. 8 [Georgian Soviet Encyclopaedia, Vol. 8]|date=1984|publisher=Metsniereba|location=Tbilisi|page=693|language=Georgian|chapter=სალიპარტიანო [Salipartiano]}}</ref> According to the historian [[Cyril Toumanoff]], they were accepted among the [[knyaz|princely nobility]] of the [[Russian Empire]] in 1903.<ref>[[Cyril Toumanoff|Toumanoff, Cyril]] (1967). ''Studies in Christian Caucasian History'', p. 272. [[Georgetown University Press]].</ref>

