| genre = {{flatlist| * [[Hard rock]] * [[Heavy metal music|heavy metal]] }} | occupation = Musician, singer | years_active = 2003–present | instrument = Guitar, vocals | label = [[Warner Music Group|Warner Music]], Masterjam, (PBP) Panggau Buluh Pengerindu | associated_acts = {{flatlist| * [[Masterpiece (band)|Masterpiece]] }} }}
'''Kennedy Edwin''' is an [[Iban language|Iban]] musician who serves as the rhythm and vocals for [[Borneo|Bornean]] hard rock band [[Masterpiece (band)|Masterpiece]]. Along with his brother [[Willy Edwin]], he is one of the founding members of [[Masterpiece (band)|Masterpiece]], and has since released five studio albums with the band.<ref name="background1">{{cite web|last=Biography|first=Masterpiece's Biography|title=The Band- Masterpiece Iban Rock Band Biography|url=http://www.ibanband.blogspot.com/2012/07/masterpiece-iban-band-biography.html}}</ref><ref name="EarlyYears">{{cite web|last1=Music revolution|first1=Masterpiece|title=Masterpiece - Iban indie rock music revolution|url=http://nocturneofmine.blogspot.in/2010/07/masterpiece-iban-indie-rock-music.html|publisher=World Of Nocturne}}</ref><ref name="newalbum2016">{{cite web|last1=Masterpiece|first1=new album|title=Ngarap Ka Nuan Nikal Pulai album officially released|url=http://seeds.theborneopost.com/2016/03/21/masterpiece-looks-forward-to-inject-new-life-into-sarawaks-music-industry/|website=Borneo Post news|publisher=The Borneo Post|accessdate=21 March 2016}}</ref>
==Personal life== Kennedy Edwin was born in [[Kanowit]], and raised in the town of [[Sibu]], [[Sarawak]].
==Career== ===Masterpiece (2003–present)=== {{Main article|Masterpiece (band)}} Kennedy Edwin is a founding member of the [[Borneo|Bornean]] hard rock band [[Masterpiece (band)|Masterpiece]] (''Masterjam'' 2003–2005). He formed the band with his brother [[Willy Edwin]] (lead guitar) in 2003 along with Watt Marcus and Roni joining as bassist and drummer, respectively. Edwin was the lead singer for the band until 2005, when he began to focus on his guitar playing, he and Willy recruited Depha as the vocalist for the band. To date, Edwin still sang and played guitar on the tours associated with the band.<ref name="background1" />
