'''Sallie''' or '''Salomon Kok''', was an [[Antwerp]] diamond dealer from the 20th century, of Jewish-[[Dutch (ethnic group)|Dutch]] descent, who played a role in the [[Flemish Movement]].
Politically, he was rather to the left. Kok became an important investor to the [[Flamenpolitik|Flemish activists]]. Activist publications were financed by him.<ref name="Secessie">[[Paul Beliën]], [http://www.secessie.nu/pdf/7-3.pdf ''Een mythe doorprikt: Vlaanderen als bakermat van racisme en antisemitisme''] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110724191047/http://www.secessie.nu/pdf/7-3.pdf |date=24 July 2011 }} (''A Myth renounced. Flanders as the cradle of racism and anti-Semitism''), in ''Secessie, Kwartaalblad voor de Studie van Separatisme en Directe Democratie'' (''Secession, quarterly for the Study of Separatism and Direct Democracy), April–May–June 2002, p. 28</ref><ref name ="P.Belien158">Paul Beliën, ''A Throne in Brussels. Britain, the Saxe-Coburgs and the Belgianisation of Europe'', imprint-academic.com, 2005, p. 158</ref> Not only he supported Leo Picard’s ''Vlaamsche Post'', spokesman for the radical activists, but in 1917 he was also one of the sponsors of a delegation of socialist activists to the international socialist peace conference in [[Stockholm]]. Like [[Marten Rudelsheim]], he was involved in the [[Antwerp]] section of ''Volksopbeuring'' (popular relief, 1915), which supported impoverished [[Flemings]].<ref>[https://books.google.com/books?id=Ok-o6daGPDYC&pg=PA770&lpg=PA770&dq=%22Bernard+Tokkie%22&source=bl&ots=862GQfvChy&sig=PHkAMIcLbkuWf-xGcIzVeUinFnU&hl=nl&ei=g3sESuGpB826jAfHvqS7Bg&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=4#PPA88,M1, Lieven Saerens , ''Vreemdelingen in een wereldstad: een geschiedenis van Antwerpen en zijn joodse bevolking (1880-1944)''] (''Strangers in a metropolis: a history of Antwerp and its Jewish population (1880-1944))'', Ed. Lannoo, 2000, {{ISBN|90-209-4109-7}}, {{ISBN|978-90-209-4109-8}}, p. 88</ref> Kok fought for [[Flanders]] as well as for a [[Sionism|Jewish state]].
